Main figure: scatterplot of incorrect spellings to target (âassiduousâ)

This is the candidate for the figure. Here the points (labels) are jittered to minimize overlapping. Remember though that the jittering (called within the position kwarg in geom_label()) introduces randomness into rendering the plot. In order to find the just right figure for the publication, we will need to re-render the plot until we find a jittering that we are satisfied with. The reason for this jittering is that without it the misspelled forms would overlap at each level of x- and y- such that you could only see one word, and the rest would be plotted behind it.

The orthographic (x-axis) and phonological distance (y-axis) of each misspelled word from the correct (âtargetâ) spelling is shown for âassiduousâ (top row) and âkaleidoscopeâ (bottom row). The left panels show misspellings where the participant rated the target as familiar, and the right panels show those corresponding to unfamiliar ratings for the target. Target words were chosen because they exhibited variability in the familarity rating across participants, where âassiduousâ was in general a low familiarity word, and âkaleidoscopeâ was high by comparison. The origin of each plot represents the target itself, such that the distance of a given misspelling from the origin can be interpreted as the extent to which that misspelling is dissimilar from the target word either with respect to its orthographic structure (x-axis) or phonological structure (y-axis). Word labels (points) are colored based on the number of particular misspellings observed across participants. Dashed diagonals included as a reference.
